The Coalition of Maritime Transport Unions and Associations (COMTUA) has sent a warm Easter goodwill message to Christians and Nigerians in general. In a statement made available to Daily Independent in Lagos on Monday, the COMTUA National President, Hon. Adeyinka Aroyewun commended Nigerians for their peaceful coexistence in the prevailing hardship in the country. He said: “On behalf of our National Board and the entire members of our great organisation, I wish to convey our hearty felicitation and goodwill message of solidarity and love to the entire body of Christ, in Nigeria. “This year’s Easter is being celebrated against the background of very serious national challenges which are testing the faith, capacity and power of endurance of overwhelming majority of Nigerians of all faiths and religious persuasions. “It is thus an appropriate time to joyfully join our Christian compatriots in fervent prayers and to emulate the noble teachings and exemplary precepts bequeathed to us by the Prince of peace (Jesus Christ). “We, in COMTUA, are very proud of the cherished values of brotherhood and comradeship that resonate in our ranks made up of people of different religious faiths. “Therefore ours, is a shining example of tolerance, sacrifice and selflessness, all of them inestimable ingredients for achieving any meaningful and sustainable growth, development and peace. “In full appreciation of this highly valued tradition, coupled with the captivating spirit of Easter, we hereby renew our commitment to remain God-fearing in all our dealings and open-hearted in the pursuit of all our collective aspirations. Thank you and God bless.”